    <Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIVILOPEDIA_UNITS_VIETCONG_TEXT">
      <Text>
		  The Viet Cong was a political organization and army in South Vietnam and Cambodia that fought the United States and South Vietnamese governments during the Vietnam War. North Vietnam established the National Liberation Front in 1960 to foment 'anti-imperialist' insurgency in the South.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]The Viet Cong comprised a flexible mix of guerrilla and conventional warfare battle tactics, proving to be very dangerous enemy for US army. The VC/NVA battle philosophy placed great stress on learning and adaptability, and systematically strived to improve battle techniques at the lowest levels. Units and individuals were expected to be problem solvers, making creative use out of what might be fleeting opportunities and scarce resources. The Viet Cong's best-known action was the Tet Offensive, a massive assault on more than 100 South Vietnamese urban centers in 1968, which was painful tactical defeat for the Viet Cong, but a strategic victory for North Vietnam and the turning point of the war.
	  </Text>
    </Row>
